We train. We motivate. We grow. Together.
Step up your game and join the family, so we can #GymsharkTrain together 🦈

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Get ready to make that full body work with this powerful at-home HIIT workout from @mrandmrsmuscle 💪 
Tag a friend who you would duo this with!
#Gymsharktrain

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

@wozldn brings you a 🔥 full body workout to celebrate the last day of #Gymshark66! Expect 30 minutes of dynamic and energetic H.I.I.T exercises – you're defo going to need some water 🥵

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

node.text:
Want to increase your flexibility? Then try this mobility flow routine by @jessicaolie 🙌
Click the link in our bio for more mobility workouts‼️ #Gymsharktrain

node.accessibility_caption:
@adotty10 and @littletfitness perform an advanced, explosive HIIT routine, perfect for the end of your workout or as an alternative to running. He is seen wearing Gymshark Arrival Woven Joggers in light grey whilst she wears black Gymshark Vital Seamless shorts paired with a cropped white tee. There are three, 45 second exercises which have a 15 second rest in between, with a 1 minute rest between rounds. They do this for 4 rounds.
The first exercise is explosive knee jumps and bear crawls, where they start by leaping forward from a kneeling position, and running backwards in a bear crawl. The second is kick throughs. Starting in an on all fours position, they balance on one arm and leg whilst the other leg is tucked under their body and pushed out to the opposite side. They then switch leg and do the same at a fast pace. The final exercise is downward dogs. They start from a crouched position and bounce themselves forward into a press up, before coming back up into a downward dog position.

node.text:
Partner challenge time - explosive HIIT style 🏆
Who do you think can make it all the way through? You decide.
1. Explosive knee jumps + bear crawl (45 sec)
2. Kick throughs (45 sec)
3. Downward dogs (45 sec)
15 sec rest between each exercise | 1 min rest between rounds | 4 rounds
Tag a friend to challenge them ⬇️
📸: @adotty10 + @littletfitness
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Have you hit a plateau in your training? Try this 👇
Change your typical exercise routine to keep your body guessing what’s next. Your body learns to adapt to your current energy demands, until you make adjustments that force it to work in new and exciting ways 💥
Swipe and save on this new workout to get you going again.
Circuit ➡️ 12-15 reps per side | 4 sets | 30 sec rest
📸: @realrubaali
#GymsharkTrain

This tempting HIIT circuit is only 4 minutes long 😱
20s work / 10s rest / 2 rounds (or repeat as many rounds as you like!)
1️⃣ Snap jump
2️⃣ Drop squat floor touch
3️⃣ Cross jacks
4️⃣ High knee run
Tag a friend with a busy schedule so they can try this 👇
📸: @mrandmrsmuscle
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
This back and biceps routine will make upper body workouts your new fave 🙌
1️⃣ Pull-ups (3x sets)
2️⃣ Reverse grip pulldowns (3x8-10)
3️⃣ Cable rows (increase weight + decrease reps each set) (3x6-10)
Superset:
4️⃣ Chest supported rows straight into (3x10)
5️⃣ Rear delt flys (3x10)
Swipe, save and leave a comment if you're training today 💪
📸: @_brittanylupton
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Don't let weak wrists get the best of your workout! 
Try some of these exercises to improve strength + flexibility 👏
📸: @odinmkalvo
#GymsharkTrain

YES, you can fit this 8-minute pilates workout right into your weekend schedule 🙌
Swipe + save to work those lower abs alongside @movewithnicole:
1️⃣ Single leg diamond toe taps (10 reps)
2️⃣ Diamond leg toe taps (10 reps)
3️⃣ Lower body curl (10 reps)
4️⃣ Lower body curl hold (10 secs)
5️⃣ 3 Legged dog to Plank combo (5 reps each side)
#GymsharkTrain

Try this @obi_vincent #EmomWorkout during your next training day if you're looking for a mighty conditioning boost 💥
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Boost your mood by taking your next workout outdoors. You won't regret it! 🌞
Be sure to use this boss @hxhails HIIT session when you get there:
1️⃣ Banded squat to side kick
2️⃣ Squat to kick back
3️⃣ Criss cross squat jumps
4️⃣ Squat jump w/ arm swing
Tag a gym buddy who would join you for this one 👭
#GymsharkTrain
